CHARACTERS, PLACES, AND INCIDENTS
IN THIS PRODUCTION ARE PARTLY FICTITIOUS

2
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:11,240
VIEWER DISCRETION IS ADVISED

3
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,120
{\an8}Now you're asking for it!

4
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:03,160
{\an8}- Let go!
- Stop!

5
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,760
{\an8}Let go!

6
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:08,759
{\an8}Let go…

7
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,400
{\an8}How come you came with Mr. Pat last night?

8
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,520
{\an8}It's a long story, Thee.

9
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:19,240
{\an8}Yesterday I saw Mr. Anapat and Mook.
They seemed really close.

10
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:21,600
{\an8}Does he have a crush on her too?

11
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,360
{\an8}I'm really worried about you, you know?

12
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:25,880
{\an8}Don't risk your life like that again.

13
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:30,800
{\an8}I wouldn't know what to do
if something were to happen to you.

14
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:58,480
Where have I seen this kid before?

15
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:10,280
Ms. Narin!

16
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,560
Ms. Narin!

17
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,280
Are you alright?

18
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:18,800
I just got a little lightheaded.

19
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:20,800
Let me make you a new cup.

20
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:21,880
It's alright.

21
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:25,040
I think you should sit down. Let's go.

22
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,880
- Watch out for the glass.
- Thank you.

23
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,920
Easy, okay?

24
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,080
I'm really sorry, Ms. Mook.

25
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:42,880
I wanted to take care of you,

26
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:45,160
but now you have to take care of me.

27
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,960
Don't worry about it.

28
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:52,000
Last time we met,
you didn't seem so well either.

29
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,240
Do you have a medical condition?

30
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:57,400
I have a heart disease.

31
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:01,320
I've been thinking, once I've done
what I always wanted to,

32
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,960
I'll finally retire.

33
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:05,960
Okay.

34
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:11,160
You're feeling better now, right?

35
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:21,120
I'm trying to contain my emotions.

36
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,240
About Mr. Thee, right?

37
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,320
Yes.

38
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:34,080
You know, sometimes it's like a test.

39
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:38,280
If it's meant to be yours, it'll be.

40
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:44,360
But if it's not meant to be mine,

41
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,360
I should take a step back, right?

42
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:02,160
Okay.

43
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:33,440
Prao, where's our son?

44
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:40,320
If you're home this late,

45
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,080
of course he'd be in bed already.

46
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:44,840
You told me Pun's sick.

47
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:47,120
Is he okay?

48
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:52,120
If I didn't use him as an excuse,

49
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,880
you'd never come home, would you?

50
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,560
Explain this.

51
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:05,440
Besides Mook, you're seeing
other girls too, Pat?

52
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,480
You've misunderstood me.

53
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,760
What?

54
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:11,760
Do I need proof of you two in the same bed
before you'll admit it?

55
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:21,360
In front of everyone,
you act like a good man,

56
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,120
but in reality,

57
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:27,200
you're just a scumbag
who left your family to have an affair!

58
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:29,480
Don't bother asking me, Prao,

59
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,640
if you won't believe a single word I say.

60
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:33,960
I'm not stupid!

61
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:36,680
I could tell from the photo
how close you two really are.

62
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:42,040
You've had too much to drink.

63
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,200
Let's talk later.

64
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:49,120
If you have someone else,
just admit it. Is that so hard, Pat?

65
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:57,560
The problem's got nothing to do
with anyone, Prao.

66
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:05,360
The problem is that you never trust me.

67
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,200
You never listened to me

68
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:10,080
or agreed with anything I said.

69
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:13,000
You just want me to be
what you want me to be.

70
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:18,160
You should ask yourself
if you still even want me.

71
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:42,120
Mook.

72
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,520
Mook.

73
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:55,320
Mook, can we talk things out?

74
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,440
FAVORITES
MOOK - MR. PITAK

75
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:06,800
MOOK - CALLING…

76
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:59,520
<i>You can cash out however much you'd like.</i>

77
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:02,200
Think of it as a bonus
I'm paying in advance.

78
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:05,320
Then, come work with me
officially already.

79
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:08,080
As for your travel agency,
if you want to keep running it,

80
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:09,360
that's fine by me.

81
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,360
But do it as a hobby,

82
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:14,560
or ask someone you trust
to run it for you.

83
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,400
Please accept it.

84
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:19,080
Because if you don't,

85
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:22,280
who knows when you'll finally solve
your company's problems.

86
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,680
<i>I'm not stupid!</i>

87
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:29,480
I could tell from the photo
how close you two really are.

88
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:33,720
If you have someone else,
just admit it. Is that so hard, Pat?

89
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,960
CONTACTS

90
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,400
MOOK

91
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:46,080
Thank you for coming.

92
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:11,360
Aren't you going to ask me
why I called you?

93
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:15,720
It's because you feel comfortable
with me, of course.

94
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:20,440
I feel the same way when I'm with you.

95
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,640
How ironic.

96
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:33,600
I don't even feel this way with the one

97
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,160
I should feel it with.

98
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,960
My wife, I mean.

99
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,080
Ms. Veluree's already checked out, sir.

100
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:00,040
Okay.

101
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,480
MOOK

102
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:17,200
Ms. Mook's already left this morning.

103
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:18,440
Her friends picked her up.

104
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:22,280
Mr. Thee.

105
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:31,960
If you can't make her happy,
then you should let her go.

106
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,960
This is my problem.

107
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,480
I can deal with it myself.

108
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:42,080
You should get ready
to solve your own problems.

109
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:56,720
- Here's your coffee.
- Thank you.

110
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:02,080
Drank too much last night?

111
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:07,040
It's been a while since my last time,
so I'm a bit dizzy.

112
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,480
Is Mook here yet?

113
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,320
No, she isn't.

114
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,240
Can you tell her to see me
once she's here?

115
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:16,800
Of course, Mr. Pat.

116
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:18,040
Thanks.

117
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:32,280
<i>I have a wife and a kid,</i>

118
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:35,880
but my family's falling apart.

119
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:42,760
I've heard a bit of your background.

120
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:49,440
I wouldn't judge someone
because of this, though.

121
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:59,400
What do you really want from me?

122
00:14:03,520 --> 00:14:04,800
I like you.

123
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:10,200
You're always helping me.

124
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:13,320
You're a kind person.

125
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:17,360
Sometimes you even worry about me
more than yourself.

126
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:25,000
I don't care what your past is like.

127
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:30,200
Because for me, who you are today
is the best version of yourself.

128
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:01,600
What have I done?

129
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,560
Are you hungover, Boss?

130
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:28,400
Is it that obvious, Mook?

131
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:30,320
How come everyone could tell?

132
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,880
So, how's the situation?

133
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:41,320
I made a list of all the changes needed.

134
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:43,480
I'll brief the team on it later.

135
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:47,560
I meant your situation with Mr. Thee.

136
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:52,440
It's really nothing.

137
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,840
I'll just keep doing my job.

138
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,640
Anyway, I should get back to work.

139
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,440
Boss,

140
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:08,640
need some hangover pills?

141
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:12,640
Okay. I'll go now.

142
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:30,040
So?

143
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:32,000
I found you some clients.

144
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,160
- Amazing, right?
- Maybe

145
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:34,560
- lobsters.
- Yeah.

146
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:37,680
You sure about this, Ma?

147
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,920
Yeah, Ma,

148
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,320
if they have a heart attack
and die during the tour,

149
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,760
then we're screwed, Ma.

150
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,520
Watch your mouth!

151
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:50,360
Isn't it you who made us lose clients?

152
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:53,080
That's why I had to find you new clients!

153
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:55,520
It wasn't my fault, Ma.

154
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,400
You should blame them for being so picky.

155
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,920
They kept asking for stuff.

156
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,120
They wanted everything free.

157
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,640
Enough, enough!

158
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,200
I don't want to hear it.

159
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:04,960
Just do a better job this time.

160
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,480
You're lucky you have clients.

161
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:08,520
Plus,

162
00:17:08,599 --> 00:17:11,200
they're all my friends,

163
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,800
and they're loaded.

164
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,520
If you give them good service,

165
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:16,720
they'll tip you like crazy.

166
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,760
You hear me?

167
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:20,760
Come on. Let's get in our van!

168
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:22,000
- Let's go!
- Yes!

169
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:23,760
- In the van!
- Go, go!

170
00:17:23,839 --> 00:17:25,359
- Let's go.
- Yes!

171
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:28,400
This won't be easy.

172
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:31,760
Thank you!

173
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:33,360
Don't worry, Kuk.

174
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:38,480
I'll handle them to compensate you
for losing those clients.

175
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:39,400
Okay?

176
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:44,480
Let's go!

177
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:45,640
Ugh!

178
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:46,680
Oh my!

179
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:48,240
- Fine, come on.
- Restroom!

180
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:49,040
What now, Ma?

181
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:51,680
- I need to pee!
- I need to pee!

182
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:52,720
Okay, please relax.

183
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,520
- The restroom's that way.
- Where?

184
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:56,320
- Let's go.
- Okay, let's go.

185
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:58,400
- Ugh.
- Whoa.

186
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:01,200
Go take care of your clients, yeah?

187
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:02,720
Ugh.

188
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:06,920
- Give me one!
- Give me one!

189
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,120
- Calm down, everyone.
- Give me one!

190
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,920
- You can go light them over there.
- There?

191
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,480
- Oh, I'll get one from you then.
- Calm down, okay?

192
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,480
- Move.
- Move, kids!

193
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:17,400
- Elders go first!
- You can do it after.

194
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,880
Here we come.

195
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,160
Make way!

196
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:34,040
- Move, people, move!
- Come on.

197
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:36,920
- Let us get in there!
- Move.

198
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,040
- Let me walk there!
- Move!

199
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:39,760
- Okay.
- Move. Get out of the way!

200
00:18:39,840 --> 00:18:42,520
Bless me with good health
and lots of wealth.

201
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:43,800
Good things only.

202
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,920
Bless me.

203
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,400
- What are you doing?!
- No!

204
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:48,960
I haven't finished!

205
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:51,360
- Hey!
- Don't fight.

206
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:01,320
What? Auntie!

207
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,480
How could you do that?

208
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:03,680
See, I'm all wet now.

209
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:06,000
What happened, Hua?

210
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:08,040
She said I splashed water on her.

211
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:10,600
I didn't! I was just washing my hands.

212
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:15,000
I'm sorry.

213
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:17,280
My friend probably didn't mean it.

214
00:19:17,360 --> 00:19:18,840
Let's just forget it, okay?

215
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:20,400
Don't apologize to them, Tiansee.

216
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:22,520
Forget it. Come on. Let's get in our van.

217
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:24,320
Come on. Let's go.

218
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,200
Oops. Sorry, Auntie.

219
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:28,520
I didn't mean it either.

220
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:31,080
My goodness! How dare you?

221
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:32,960
Oh, Auntie.

222
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:35,160
Now you're asking for it. Sure then!

223
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:39,600
- You!
- How could you!

224
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:41,920
No, stop!

225
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,840
Don't!

226
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:51,000
- Ma'am, please stop.
- Stop it!

227
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:57,920
- Ma!
- Please stop, ma'am!

228
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:04,600
Hey!

229
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:07,480
Hey! You want this?!

230
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:12,640
Khim, I take it you've heard

231
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:16,560
that the company's put together
a committee to look into…

232
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:22,760
Yes, I'm well aware.

233
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:28,400
You have to admit that your story

234
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:31,440
and the word that got out
are very serious,

235
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:35,560
and they could damage
our company's reputation.

236
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:40,560
But on the other hand,
your story also started

237
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:44,120
something influential on social media.

238
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:47,600
People have made so many posts

239
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:51,400
to support you and commend you
for your bravery.

240
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,120
Plus,

241
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:56,200
Preaw already told me everything.

242
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:02,200
I heard you and Khim
were threatened by that man.

243
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:03,400
Is it true?

244
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:06,880
Yes, but please don't fire Khim, Kwan.

245
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:08,280
If it weren't for her,

246
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:11,320
I never would've dared
to stand up to that evil man.

247
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:15,040
But there's also a video
he took of her, isn't there?

248
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:18,920
Yes, but she isn't a coward like me,

249
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,960
who kept hiding
because I was too scared to see anyone,

250
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:25,760
and I allowed that evil man
to go on and hurt others.

251
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:33,320
I understand
that you were also a victim, Khim.

252
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:36,840
And we wanted to see you today

253
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:40,680
to inform you that our company's
reached a decision on your issue.

254
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:42,880
We agreed that…

255
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:52,080
you can keep working here,

256
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:55,560
and the situation won't disqualify you

257
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:58,840
from being considered for a promotion.

258
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:04,560
Thank you.

259
00:22:05,120 --> 00:22:06,600
I really appreciate it.

260
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:08,520
But, Khim,

261
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:12,080
I hope what happened

262
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:15,280
can be a lesson and a reminder for you

263
00:22:15,360 --> 00:22:17,560
to never repeat the same mistake.

264
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:20,280
Yes, Kwan,

265
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:23,360
I'll make sure it doesn't happen again.

266
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:41,680
What's up, Usa?

267
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:46,640
What? They got arrested?

268
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,720
Ugh! Please be quiet!

269
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,040
Please wait your turn. You first.

270
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,120
What's all this about, Ma?

271
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,560
Did you pick a fight with them?

272
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:00,760
They started it. I didn't.

273
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:03,000
Stop it. Quit fighting already.

274
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:05,240
Please be polite.

275
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:08,440
Kuk, let's talk to the police
and get it over with.

276
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:10,120
I'm already so embarrassed.

277
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:14,040
Don't worry about it.

278
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:16,200
We just need to pay the fines.

279
00:23:16,280 --> 00:23:18,880
Let bygones be bygones, okay, Kuk?

280
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:21,520
I should've asked Mook for help
in the first place.

281
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:22,920
Our clients would've returned,

282
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:26,280
and we wouldn't have lost our time,
money, and reputation like this!

283
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:29,440
- Please?
- Quiet down. Please don't fight.

284
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:31,080
Excuse me. Hello.

285
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:33,680
I'll compensate for everything.

286
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,000
Here are your fines.

287
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:44,560
You'll be fined 500 baht each
on charges of affray.

288
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:48,080
I want to meet Mr. Thee's mom.

289
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:51,320
Why would you want to meet her?

290
00:23:52,560 --> 00:23:54,360
Haven't you heard of that saying?

291
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:56,920
"Trample a man when he's down."

292
00:23:57,480 --> 00:24:00,760
Once I tell her about Mook,

293
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:06,120
surely, it'll be over for Mook.

294
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:08,280
Good idea, Ma.

295
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:10,960
That way, we'll also tank her company,

296
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:13,200
and we'll replace them.

297
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:18,960
Now that's what I call
killing two birds with one stone.

298
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:23,480
I'll call Mrs. Anna tomorrow
to set a date for you.

299
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:33,240
Come on in.

300
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:35,600
Mook, Mr. Pitak's here to see you.

301
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,600
Sorry to bother you, Ms. Mook.

302
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:52,640
No worries, Mr. Pitak.

303
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:54,640
If you'll excuse me.

304
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:55,720
Sure.

305
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:04,360
What was he doing here? He looked serious.

306
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:07,320
Please call a meeting with the team.

307
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:08,360
I'll tell everyone.

308
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:18,760
It's not that, is it?

309
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:20,680
Or maybe it is?

310
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:25,280
We need to find a new model
for the wedding campaign?

311
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:26,920
Yes,

312
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:30,320
TJ group wants Ms. Bella to model
alongside Mr. Thee.

313
00:25:31,080 --> 00:25:35,080
But both the pictures for the ad
and the content are almost done!

314
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,960
Our content stays the same,

315
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,960
but we'll need to reshoot the pictures,

316
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:42,080
because retouching them
would be too difficult.

317
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:43,880
Let's just reshoot the whole thing.

318
00:25:43,960 --> 00:25:45,400
Can you schedule it?

319
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:46,520
Mook, but--

320
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:48,080
Just do it.

321
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:49,680
It's what our client wants.

322
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:55,960
Come to think of it,

323
00:25:56,040 --> 00:25:58,840
Ms. Bella's better suited
for this campaign than me.

324
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:08,800
Scrap the pictures of me and Mr. Thee,
and make a new layout.

325
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:10,920
Please make those edits and let me know.

326
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:13,440
Got it.

327
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:20,000
Don't tell Boss about this.

328
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:22,440
If something comes up,
come to me directly.

329
00:26:23,880 --> 00:26:24,720
Okay, Mook.

330
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:25,720
Okay.

331
00:26:31,320 --> 00:26:32,600
For sure.

332
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:35,840
Mr. Thee's mom
ordered this change, for sure.

333
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:39,080
Isn't this going a bit too far?

334
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:42,800
Does she plan on hurting them so much
that it's awkward for them?

335
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:45,240
We can't help it.

336
00:26:45,320 --> 00:26:49,280
We're just his partner,
but that's his actual fiancée.

337
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:51,800
Let's get this over with.

338
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:54,440
At least Mook can finally be free
from all this.

339
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,520
How harsh.

340
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:01,800
What do we need to redo now?

341
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:02,800
- A lot.
- Everything.

342
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:05,040
- We have to start all over.
- Just a lot.

343
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:07,520
From the beginning.

344
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:11,320
Did my mom tell you to tell Mook that?

345
00:27:12,680 --> 00:27:13,920
Yes, Mr. Thee.

346
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,160
I'm really sorry.

347
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:25,280
It's no use, Mr. Thee.

348
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:30,200
Every time you refuse,

349
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:34,120
Ms. Mook's the one who ends up in trouble.

350
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:39,440
Mrs. Anna will do anything to get her way.

351
00:27:41,120 --> 00:27:44,760
If you don't want Ms. Mook
to get hurt any more than this,

352
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:49,520
this isn't the way to go up against her.

353
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:13,200
Thank you for taking the time
to meet us, Mrs. Anna.

354
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,680
This is Mrs. Tiansee.

355
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:20,080
She's the mother of Mr. Apichart,
the CEO of Family Tour and Travel.

356
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:24,040
She also used to be
Ms. Veluree's mother-in-law.

357
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:28,960
So you both know Ms. Veluree too?

358
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:31,720
That's an understatement.

359
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:36,000
You could say
I know her from the inside out.

360
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:40,600
I wanted to meet you today

361
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:43,640
because my son's made the same mistake.

362
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:48,280
That's why I'm worried about Mr. Thee,

363
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:51,280
since I'm a mother like you.

364
00:28:55,760 --> 00:29:00,080
That woman turned my son
into someone else entirely.

365
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:04,280
She did that to your son too, didn't she?

366
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:11,720
I made the wrong decision.

367
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:16,640
At first, I thought Veluree
seemed pretty innocent.

368
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:19,960
I always love whoever my son loves.

369
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:23,080
But once they got married
and moved in together…

370
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:27,920
it turned out that woman's very scary.

371
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:31,920
When I heard she's been nagging Mr. Thee,

372
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:35,840
I wanted to warn you.

373
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:43,720
Actually, I could kind of tell

374
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:47,400
what her intention was
for getting close to Mr. Thee.

375
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:50,320
Don't worry,

376
00:29:50,840 --> 00:29:53,520
I won't let anyone fool my son.

377
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:58,400
If I can help you with anything,
please let me know.

378
00:29:58,480 --> 00:29:59,560
I'd be happy to help.

379
00:30:01,560 --> 00:30:04,440
Too bad we didn't meet earlier.

380
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:08,480
Otherwise, when Thee
was deciding the winner for his project,

381
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:12,160
Family Tour and Travel might've won.

382
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:18,280
How about this?

383
00:30:18,360 --> 00:30:20,840
I have another project
you might be interested in.

384
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:24,680
I can send you the details
if you're interested.

385
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:26,680
Really?

386
00:30:44,840 --> 00:30:47,280
- Would this work?
- It's good.

387
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:49,200
Let me take a look for you.

388
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,480
- Okay.
- Alright.

389
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:02,480
Mook, I could've handled this shoot alone.

390
00:31:02,560 --> 00:31:03,560
It's just a few shots.

391
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:06,240
It's better for me to be here.

392
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:08,520
This way, we can finalize it,
and no one has to wait.

393
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:16,000
What, Whan?

394
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:18,360
Do I seem that weak?

395
00:31:25,920 --> 00:31:27,080
No, Mook.

396
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:29,120
If all those crazy things
were to happen to me,

397
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:31,640
I don't think I can stay as strong as you.

398
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:35,000
Alright?

399
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:44,480
Good morning.

400
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:46,520
Is everything all set?

401
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:48,520
Yes, we're all set here.

402
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:52,240
Sorry for the changes.

403
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:56,200
If we published those photos
of you and Thee,

404
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:57,440
it'd cause misunderstandings.

405
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:02,840
After all, his real fiancée's
already made an appearance,

406
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:06,080
so we should do things properly.

407
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:31,160
The concept for today's shoot
is a couple who's soon to be married.

408
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:34,480
The vibe should be relaxed and natural.

409
00:32:44,120 --> 00:32:46,760
Let's get it over with, Thee. Let's go.

410
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:56,880
Let's try this.
A bit closer to each other, please.

411
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:58,400
- Okay.
- Okay.

412
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,680
Let's try this.

413
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:05,400
How is it?

414
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:07,960
- The lighting's perfect. One more, please.
- Okay, one more.

415
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:13,840
Good. A little closer
to each other, please.

416
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:14,960
Hold that pose.

417
00:33:15,040 --> 00:33:16,440
Look at the camera, please.

418
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:21,200
Can I see some romantic hand-holding?

419
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:24,640
They made changes?!

420
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:25,960
Yes.

421
00:33:26,040 --> 00:33:29,040
Mrs. Anna wanted
all the couple photos to be changed

422
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:31,040
by replacing Mook with Ms. Bella.

423
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:34,920
I feel so bad for Mook, Boss.
She's clearly messing with her.

424
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:37,160
Why didn't I know about this?

425
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:39,920
Well, Mook told us not to tell you.

426
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,120
She doesn't want you to be upset.

427
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,200
Where is she now?

428
00:33:47,360 --> 00:33:49,680
She's directing the shoot
at The One, Boss.

429
00:33:58,040 --> 00:34:00,160
We're all set. Thank you.

430
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:09,199
It's just an ad,
yet you already look this good.

431
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,560
When you do your pre-wedding shoot,

432
00:34:12,639 --> 00:34:15,440
you'll make a really pretty bride, Bell.

433
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,000
Boss!

434
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:54,560
Why didn't you tell me you made changes?

435
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:58,880
This is Mr. Anapat.

436
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:01,000
He's the CEO of A Round Trip Travel.

437
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:03,880
Good morning.

438
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:08,120
The other day, I was busy,
so we never formally met.

439
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:11,040
Good morning.

440
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:16,160
Could you tell me
why we needed to edit the ad?

441
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:21,600
If there's an error,
of course, you'd have to edit it.

442
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:24,600
If you wanted to have a model

443
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:28,080
alongside Thee for the shoot,
you should've told me first,

444
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:32,120
so you wouldn't have needed
a backup like Ms. Mook.

445
00:35:37,080 --> 00:35:39,680
For every process and every step,

446
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:42,200
we always had meetings,
and we followed briefs.

447
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:47,280
In fact, I think the original photos
with Mr. Thee and Mook

448
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:48,720
already look great.

449
00:35:51,080 --> 00:35:54,720
But you're our client,
so if you wish to make any changes,

450
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:56,480
I'm happy to oblige.

451
00:35:59,040 --> 00:36:03,440
Making changes the way Mrs. Anna sees fit
is the right thing to do.

452
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:09,080
You're done, right?

453
00:36:09,680 --> 00:36:11,360
Want to leave together?

454
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:14,880
Let's get changed so we can go.

455
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:16,120
I'm getting a bit tired.

456
00:36:24,440 --> 00:36:28,040
Then, take care of her for me, honey.

457
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:42,320
Looks like I'll have to ask you

458
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:45,200
to organize their wedding too,

459
00:36:46,040 --> 00:36:51,920
because it seems you're well aware
of what Thee likes or doesn't like.

460
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:08,320
Thank you, Boss.

461
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:13,440
You know, I can get you off this project.

462
00:37:18,240 --> 00:37:19,920
No, it's probably for the best.

463
00:37:22,560 --> 00:37:24,480
It made me see clearly

464
00:37:26,120 --> 00:37:27,600
where I really belong.

465
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:52,960
Drive safe, Boss.

466
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:56,440
Mook.

467
00:37:58,080 --> 00:38:01,360
I know that you're really worried about me

468
00:38:02,160 --> 00:38:04,120
and that you don't want
to see me get bullied.

469
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:09,080
But don't worry, Boss,

470
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:13,680
I'll try to return to my old self.

471
00:38:15,760 --> 00:38:17,640
Please give me some time.

472
00:38:22,880 --> 00:38:26,360
If I can help you with anything,
I'm always here.

473
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:31,120
Thank you, Boss.

474
00:38:35,640 --> 00:38:36,560
See you.

475
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:27,600
Let's go get changed, so we can go.

476
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:28,600
I'm getting a bit tired.

477
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:33,240
Take care of her for me, honey.

478
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,240
Hello?

479
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:07,120
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

480
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:08,360
What happened?

481
00:40:08,440 --> 00:40:11,640
The lady who came with you that day
came and canceled the reservation.

482
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:13,520
Who was she with?

483
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:17,080
She came with another man,
probably her father.

484
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:19,880
Where is she now?

485
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:21,720
She went to our sample room,

486
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:24,120
but I'm not sure if she's left yet.

487
00:41:10,480 --> 00:41:11,600
Hey.

488
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:51,920
Thank you.

489
00:42:03,600 --> 00:42:05,000
What happened?

490
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:11,520
Well, it's just what always happens.

491
00:42:13,040 --> 00:42:16,320
This is not the first time
I had to do this.

492
00:42:20,640 --> 00:42:21,880
Did your dad not like it here?

493
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:25,160
More like,

494
00:42:27,320 --> 00:42:29,280
he never likes anything I do.

495
00:42:34,280 --> 00:42:36,280
My mom really loved to draw.

496
00:42:37,440 --> 00:42:39,400
I kept watching her draw

497
00:42:39,920 --> 00:42:42,640
until her passion for art
rubbed off on me.

498
00:42:45,280 --> 00:42:48,480
But then, I lost her when I was 14.

499
00:42:51,640 --> 00:42:54,320
Since then, I've always lived with my dad.

500
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:57,680
My dad always works hard.

501
00:42:57,760 --> 00:43:00,000
{\an8}Even on the anniversary
of my mom's death each year,

502
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:04,400
my dad never went to her memorial.

503
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:10,120
<i>Whenever he sees me draw</i>

504
00:43:10,200 --> 00:43:11,880
<i>or appreciate a work of art,</i>

505
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:17,480
<i>I guess it reminds him of my mom</i>
<i>and makes him feel guilty.</i>

506
00:43:20,480 --> 00:43:24,640
When he found out I'm opening a studio
to design clothes here, he got so mad.

507
00:43:24,720 --> 00:43:27,720
<i>He told me to stop daydreaming</i>

508
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:34,120
<i>and marry Thee because he's made</i>
<i>an arrangement with Thee's parents.</i>

509
00:43:42,240 --> 00:43:44,240
So, you and Mr. Thee

510
00:43:45,360 --> 00:43:48,480
will get married like they told you to?

511
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:54,080
I only agreed to it

512
00:43:55,800 --> 00:44:00,480
so I can live my life
the way I want in exchange.

513
00:44:08,920 --> 00:44:11,880
What about you? Do you love Ms. Mook?

514
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:17,160
Yesterday, you seemed
really worried about her.

515
00:44:23,560 --> 00:44:27,160
Mr. Pitak's not at his desk,
but I already set a date.

516
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:30,240
Can you wait here a moment?

517
00:44:31,120 --> 00:44:31,960
Okay.

518
00:44:37,760 --> 00:44:40,280
You sure work fast, Mr. Chadchai.

519
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:44,280
So now I'm the largest shareholder.

520
00:44:44,360 --> 00:44:48,200
Yes, I already handled everything for you.

521
00:45:00,600 --> 00:45:01,800
Here.

522
00:45:02,400 --> 00:45:03,680
Your compensation.

523
00:45:04,440 --> 00:45:07,200
I hope it's enough for all your effort.

524
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:11,000
Okay, thank you very much, Mr. Thee.

525
00:45:11,080 --> 00:45:13,720
What are you going to do next, Mr. Thee?

526
00:45:14,960 --> 00:45:16,400
You can leave for the day.

527
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:19,120
I'll let you know what to do next.

528
00:45:19,720 --> 00:45:20,760
Sure.

529
00:45:23,560 --> 00:45:24,440
Mook!

530
00:45:29,520 --> 00:45:30,360
Come on in.

531
00:45:45,400 --> 00:45:48,200
- About yesterday--
- I'm here to present the edited work.

532
00:45:48,880 --> 00:45:50,440
Has Mr. Pitak told you?

533
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:54,520
Yes, he has.

534
00:45:57,880 --> 00:46:01,360
Mook, we need to talk. It's important.

535
00:46:01,440 --> 00:46:03,480
I'll wait for you in the meeting room.

536
00:46:33,200 --> 00:46:34,360
<i>Are you ready?</i>

537
00:46:48,160 --> 00:46:49,440
It's our home, Prao.

538
00:46:50,640 --> 00:46:54,120
I worked hard to earn money
for this house.

539
00:47:00,200 --> 00:47:01,840
Isn't it a bit too small, Pat?

540
00:47:08,880 --> 00:47:10,600
What if we have a child?

541
00:47:10,680 --> 00:47:12,400
There won't be room for our child to run.

542
00:47:14,560 --> 00:47:15,520
Plus,

543
00:47:15,600 --> 00:47:17,720
my dad already arranged a house for us.

544
00:47:25,720 --> 00:47:27,600
I actually like it here,

545
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:31,600
but if my dad saw it,
he wouldn't let me live here.

546
00:47:32,880 --> 00:47:35,720
You know how much he worries about me.

547
00:47:41,280 --> 00:47:42,600
How about this?

548
00:47:42,680 --> 00:47:45,720
You could rent out this house.

549
00:47:45,800 --> 00:47:47,760
That way, you can have some extra income.

550
00:47:54,520 --> 00:47:57,440
We're late! Let's hurry
before the traffic gets bad.

551
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:58,360
Come on.

552
00:48:14,520 --> 00:48:15,800
Whose house is this?

553
00:48:17,600 --> 00:48:18,720
It's mine.

554
00:48:34,080 --> 00:48:35,200
It looks cute.

555
00:48:38,520 --> 00:48:41,160
Why'd you bring me here?

556
00:48:42,600 --> 00:48:45,560
I wanted you to borrow it
and use it as your studio.

557
00:48:47,640 --> 00:48:48,760
Really?

558
00:48:50,080 --> 00:48:52,880
You'd really let me use this house
as my studio?

559
00:48:54,080 --> 00:48:55,000
Yes.

560
00:48:55,520 --> 00:48:57,680
I don't want you
to leave your goals behind.

561
00:49:03,480 --> 00:49:07,680
You're the first person
to encourage me to do what I love.

562
00:49:09,880 --> 00:49:12,760
Thank you for appreciating my passion.

563
00:49:14,160 --> 00:49:17,240
But it would be better
if you'd let me rent it.

564
00:49:17,320 --> 00:49:20,520
I don't want to bother you
and borrow it for free.

565
00:49:21,200 --> 00:49:22,720
Let's discuss that later.

566
00:49:22,800 --> 00:49:24,880
Why don't you take a look inside?

567
00:49:32,040 --> 00:49:34,200
Won't it be too big of a risk?

568
00:49:34,280 --> 00:49:36,440
Our company's too small for this project.

569
00:49:37,720 --> 00:49:39,640
You're always so scared.

570
00:49:39,720 --> 00:49:41,800
That's why our company never grew.

571
00:49:41,880 --> 00:49:42,800
Yeah.

572
00:49:42,880 --> 00:49:44,880
Fortune favors the bold.

573
00:49:44,960 --> 00:49:48,200
If you keep being scared,
when will you beat Mook?

574
00:49:52,600 --> 00:49:54,320
Please consider it.

575
00:49:54,400 --> 00:49:57,160
I think it's the perfect time
and opportunity for us.

576
00:49:57,760 --> 00:50:01,080
If we join the bidding
with Mrs. Anna backing us,

577
00:50:01,160 --> 00:50:02,920
we'll win, no matter what.

578
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:06,720
But for a project of that scale,

579
00:50:07,240 --> 00:50:09,920
our company still lacks
so many qualifications.

580
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:14,080
For the paperwork,
we just have to edit it however they want.

581
00:50:14,160 --> 00:50:16,040
We'll have someone helping us anyway.

582
00:50:16,920 --> 00:50:18,240
Once we win the project,

583
00:50:18,320 --> 00:50:21,280
it's never too late for us
to make a plan later.

584
00:50:26,240 --> 00:50:28,920
Stop thinking already. I've met Mrs. Anna.

585
00:50:29,000 --> 00:50:30,760
I can tell from her face
she's got good aura.

586
00:50:30,840 --> 00:50:32,160
She can definitely help us.

587
00:50:35,920 --> 00:50:36,840
Kuk,

588
00:50:37,400 --> 00:50:39,920
I can assure you, if we win this project,

589
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:42,400
Mook can never insult you again.

590
00:50:42,480 --> 00:50:44,160
Mrs. Anna even told us

591
00:50:44,240 --> 00:50:47,640
she'd get rid of A Round Trip
if we agreed to team up with her.

592
00:50:48,760 --> 00:50:49,600
Right, Ma?

593
00:51:01,200 --> 00:51:03,280
{\an8}Here's the plan I made for next year.

594
00:51:04,240 --> 00:51:07,720
Apart from The One,
we should look for more clients,

595
00:51:07,800 --> 00:51:10,520
because many countries
have opened their borders,

596
00:51:10,600 --> 00:51:14,080
and our regular clients
will probably start to travel again.

597
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:17,880
I agree.

598
00:51:18,800 --> 00:51:22,040
Then, we can adjust our tours
according to the situation

599
00:51:22,840 --> 00:51:24,800
and present them to our client as options.

600
00:51:25,920 --> 00:51:26,920
Sure.

601
00:51:39,480 --> 00:51:40,600
Yes, Ms. Bell?

602
00:51:44,480 --> 00:51:45,360
Okay.

603
00:51:50,600 --> 00:51:51,840
Ms. Bell called me.

604
00:51:55,480 --> 00:51:56,440
<i>Mook.</i>

605
00:51:58,040 --> 00:52:01,760
Don't you think Mr. Thee and his fiancée
seem a bit strange?

606
00:52:03,880 --> 00:52:05,080
How so?

607
00:52:10,480 --> 00:52:11,680
Well, the other day,

608
00:52:11,760 --> 00:52:15,000
I saw Ms. Bella went
to see Boss at his office.

609
00:52:17,240 --> 00:52:18,800
I wonder why.

610
00:52:20,920 --> 00:52:22,760
They could've been talking about work.

611
00:52:25,840 --> 00:52:28,240
But does Ms. Bella know about our work?

612
00:52:31,160 --> 00:52:33,160
It doesn't matter what she was there for.

613
00:52:33,240 --> 00:52:36,360
We should stay
out of Boss' business, got it?

614
00:52:40,480 --> 00:52:41,680
Yes.

615
00:52:41,760 --> 00:52:42,760
Alright.

616
00:52:53,640 --> 00:52:56,200
Well, I ran into her in Phuket.

617
00:52:58,000 --> 00:53:00,160
Back then, I didn't know her yet.

618
00:53:02,240 --> 00:53:07,040
Until later, at that party at The One,
I found out she's Mr. Thee's fiancée.

619
00:53:12,560 --> 00:53:14,120
She's a fascinating person.

620
00:53:16,720 --> 00:53:18,360
She seems really confident,

621
00:53:20,720 --> 00:53:22,160
but I feel bad for her sometimes.

622
00:53:31,680 --> 00:53:33,320
You like Ms. Bell, don't you?

623
00:53:38,360 --> 00:53:43,240
I could tell just from your eyes
how you feel about her.

624
00:53:51,200 --> 00:53:52,880
What about Mr. Thee?

625
00:53:52,960 --> 00:53:54,160
Are you sure about your decision?

626
00:53:55,640 --> 00:53:57,200
You sure changed the topic fast.

627
00:53:59,320 --> 00:54:00,760
Let's forget about that.

628
00:54:01,280 --> 00:54:04,200
It's good to just let things be.

629
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:06,160
So.

630
00:54:06,240 --> 00:54:09,600
What about Ms. Bell? What will you do now?

631
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:17,640
Does Mrs. Prao know yet?

632
00:54:45,200 --> 00:54:46,120
Yes, Bee?

633
00:54:46,640 --> 00:54:50,920
<i>The rental unit told me</i>
<i>Ms. Bella already canceled her lease.</i>

634
00:54:51,000 --> 00:54:51,880
Really?

635
00:54:52,800 --> 00:54:53,880
Okay.

636
00:54:54,400 --> 00:54:55,880
Please keep an eye out.

637
00:54:55,960 --> 00:54:57,480
Call me if anything comes up.

638
00:54:58,000 --> 00:54:59,520
<i>Got it, Prao.</i>

639
00:55:15,160 --> 00:55:16,600
Is this one good?

640
00:55:18,120 --> 00:55:19,960
This one's blurry.

641
00:55:20,040 --> 00:55:20,880
Yeah.

642
00:55:32,600 --> 00:55:33,800
May,

643
00:55:33,880 --> 00:55:35,800
I wish you could see Mook's face that day

644
00:55:35,880 --> 00:55:37,960
at the shoot with Mr. Thee and Ms. Bella.

645
00:55:38,040 --> 00:55:39,720
I felt so bad for her.

646
00:55:39,800 --> 00:55:41,640
The vibe was like a battlefield.

647
00:55:41,720 --> 00:55:43,400
Everyone was throwing bombs at each other.

648
00:55:43,480 --> 00:55:44,840
- Really?
- Yeah.

649
00:55:46,080 --> 00:55:47,720
Mook already agreed to back off.

650
00:55:47,800 --> 00:55:49,280
She didn't have to go so far.

651
00:55:49,360 --> 00:55:51,760
And what's more,

652
00:55:51,840 --> 00:55:56,360
the knight in shining armor
who came and save Mook was Boss.

653
00:55:58,120 --> 00:56:02,080
Boss probably did that to defend her

654
00:56:02,160 --> 00:56:03,920
from that kind of situation.

655
00:56:05,520 --> 00:56:06,760
You're right.

656
00:56:15,680 --> 00:56:17,480
Poor Mook.

657
00:56:17,560 --> 00:56:19,560
She shouldn't have to face any of this.

658
00:56:22,040 --> 00:56:23,200
Isn't she here yet?

659
00:56:25,160 --> 00:56:28,240
She's wrapping up the project
with Mr. Thee so we can finalize it today.

660
00:56:28,960 --> 00:56:32,400
Poor Mook. And here I thought
she finally found someone good,

661
00:56:32,480 --> 00:56:33,880
yet now she has to face all this.

662
00:56:33,960 --> 00:56:35,760
She probably won't date for a while.

663
00:56:57,120 --> 00:56:59,400
{\an8}That woman's got nothing to do with me.

664
00:57:00,640 --> 00:57:01,640
{\an8}Saifah!

665
00:57:06,840 --> 00:57:09,160
{\an8}If he'll choose a woman like you over me,

666
00:57:09,240 --> 00:57:12,600
{\an8}who adopted him, then so be it.

667
00:57:15,680 --> 00:57:18,880
{\an8}But if you're hoping to marry into money,

668
00:57:19,520 --> 00:57:20,960
{\an8}then dream on.

669
00:58:12,480 --> 00:58:14,680
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

